# Prisma migrations are generated, immutable, and checksummed by Prisma.
# Their bytes must stay identical across the public repo and downstream forks,
# so git must not flag (or try to auto-fix) whitespace in them — e.g. a
# trailing blank line at EOF would otherwise trip `git diff --check` on merge.
prisma/migrations/**/*.sql -whitespace

# ESM scripts are imported by vitest tests as well as run via `node`. A CRLF
# checkout (Windows autocrlf) of a shebang line breaks vite-node's import of
# the module, so these always materialise with LF.
scripts/*.mjs text eol=lf

# The schema is hand-edited (AGENTS.md "Change Discipline") and is the file most
# likely to be ported between the public repo and its forks. A Windows editor
# silently rewriting it to CRLF turns a 14-line change into a ~9,400-line diff
# that conflicts on every line at the next port (#2129), so pin it to LF.
prisma/schema.prisma text eol=lf

# The hand-edited markdown carries the same hazard as the schema, and `AGENTS.md`
# / `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` / `CHANGELOG.md` are the files most often ported
# between the public repo and its forks. A Windows editor rewriting one to CRLF
# turned a 28-line change into an 848-line diff, destroyed blame, and made
# `git diff --check` flag every line as trailing whitespace (#2162). Pin the
# whole set to LF rather than waiting to relearn this per file.
*.md text eol=lf

# Source files carry the same hazard, and it has now bitten three times: the
# schema (#2129), the markdown above (#2162), and two source files on the
# #2160 branch — where a CRLF flip in a test file was independently read as
# "harmless re-indentation" by three separate reviews, because `git diff -w`
# ignores whitespace INCLUDING the carriage return and so reports clean on
# exactly the churn that matters. Every tracked source file on `main` is
# already LF, so pinning the set is zero-churn today and ends the class.
*.ts text eol=lf
*.tsx text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.mjs text eol=lf
*.cjs text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.css text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
